---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Privacy Policy | truckaccidentcalc.com';
const description = 'How truckaccidentcalc.com handles visitor information, cookies, analytics, and advertising data.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><em>Last updated: May 2026.</em></p>

  <p>This page explains what information we collect when you use truckaccidentcalc.com, how we use it, and what choices you have about it. It is written to be readable, not lawyerly. The underlying compliance posture is GDPR + CCPA for visitors in jurisdictions where those apply.</p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>

  <h3>What you give us directly</h3>
  <p>We collect what you send us. If you email the editorial team at <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> we receive your email address and message contents. We don't have signup forms, comment sections, or user accounts on this site.</p>

  <h3>What our calculator does</h3>
  <p>The settlement calculator on our homepage runs entirely in your browser. Numbers you enter are <em>not</em> sent to our server, not stored, not logged, and not transmitted to third parties. Close the tab and they are gone.</p>

  <h3>Server logs and analytics</h3>
  <p>Our hosting provider records standard server access logs (IP address, request URL, user agent, timestamp) for security and reliability purposes. We may use a privacy-respecting analytics tool to count page views and understand which pages are popular. We do not use Google Analytics with default settings and we do not build behavioral profiles of individual visitors.</p>

  <h3>Advertising</h3>
  <p>This site shows ads through Google AdSense. Google and its advertising partners use cookies and similar technologies to serve ads based on a visitor's prior visits to our site and other sites. You can opt out of personalized advertising at <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a> or at <a href="https://www.aboutads.info" rel="noopener">aboutads.info</a>. For visitors in the EU/EEA/UK, AdSense's <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" rel="noopener">partner site policy</a> describes the legal basis and your rights.</p>

  <h2>How we use what we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Email you send us:</strong> we use it to respond to your message. We don't add you to a mailing list. We don't share it with anyone outside our small editorial team unless you tell us to.</li>
    <li><strong>Server logs:</strong> security, abuse prevention, debugging, and very rough traffic understanding.</li>
    <li><strong>Advertising cookies:</strong> set and read by Google and its ad partners, not by us. We don't have access to who you are individually; AdSense reports give us aggregate ad performance data only.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we don't do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>We do not sell your information.</strong> We do not have a paid lead-generation business and do not transfer visitor data to attorneys, insurance companies, or marketing firms.</li>
    <li><strong>We do not track you for case intake.</strong> Numbers entered into the calculator stay in your browser. We don't know what you typed.</li>
    <li><strong>We do not have user accounts.</strong> Nothing on this site requires a login.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Your choices</h2>
  <p>Browser-level: most modern browsers let you block third-party cookies, which limits AdSense's ability to personalize ads. The site works fine with cookies blocked &mdash; you'll still see ads, they just won't be personalized.</p>
  <p>Cookie-level: <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a> lets you turn off personalized advertising while keeping the rest of your Google experience.</p>
  <p>For GDPR / UK GDPR rights (access, rectification, erasure, portability, objection, restriction) or CCPA rights (know, delete, opt out of sale, non-discrimination), email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the subject line <code>[PRIVACY REQUEST]</code>. We respond within the legally required window for the applicable jurisdiction.</p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>This site is not directed at children under 16 and we don't knowingly collect information from children. If you believe a child has sent us information, email us and we will delete it.</p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>If we materially change how we handle visitor data, we'll update this page and update the "last updated" date at the top.</p>

  <h2>Contact about privacy</h2>
  <p>Privacy questions: <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with subject line <code>[PRIVACY]</code>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
